<h4 id="section-label">class <span>string</span></h4>
<p>
  Assigns a custom CSS class to the modal.
</p>


<h4 id="section-isopen">style <span>string</span></h4>
<p>
  The aesthetic style of the modal.
</p>

<h5>Values</h5>
<ul class="defaults">
  <li>default (defaut)</li>
  <li>full</li>
</ul>
<p>
  Additional styles can be added via CSS. See {{link-to "Theming" "documentation.theming"}}
</p>

<div class="output">
  {{eui-button label='Default' action='showModal'}}
  {{eui-button label='Full' action='showFullModal'}}
</div>


<h4 id="section-open">open <span>boolean</span></h4>
<p>
  Used to show and hide the modal when used as a block element. Defaults to <em>false</em> so if you want to show the dialog as soon as the relevant route is visited then you should set it to <em>true</em>.
</p>


<h4 id="section-targetobject">targetObject <span>object</span></h4>
<p>
  Only used if creating the modal programmatically. It sets the target for events triggered within the modal. Set it equal to <em>this</em> to have events handled in the context that opens the modal.
</p>


<h4 id="section-accept">accept <span>string</span></h4>
<p>
  You may manually call this action using regular action syntax. Only available if modal was created programatically.
</p>


<h4 id="section-cancel">cancel <span>string</span></h4>
<p>
  This action is automatically called if the user closes the dialog by pressing <em>esc</em>. If you created your modal programatically you may manually call this action using regular action syntax.
</p>
